comments: too disorganized and lots of work. probably not worth it unless you really, really want to take L5.
Good course, great instructor, I'd recommend it
Definitely take this class. I feel like it really helped improve my reading and writing skills. More work intensive than L3 and L4 but Seemaji is great.
Take this! Hindi is the best language at Yale.

Hindi L5 is a delight. Seema ji is very kind and accommodates different skill levels well. The amount of homework is fairly consistent (about 3 hours the day before class, for me, as a non-native speaker) but flexible if you are in crisis for another class.
